text.section:
"Consumer commodity" means any food, drug, device, or cosmetic that is not:
Tobacco or a tobacco product;
A commodity that is subject to packaging or labeling requirements imposed under the Federal Insecticide, Fungicide, and Rodenticide Act or the federal Animal Virus, Serum, Toxin, Antitoxin Act;
A drug that is subject to the provisions of § 353(b)(1) of the federal act;
A beverage that is subject to or complies with packaging or labeling requirements imposed by the federal Bureau of Alcohol, Tobacco and Firearms; or
A seed or other commodity that is subject to the provisions of §§ 9-206 through 9-213 of the Agriculture Article.
